sometimes we want to compare two different commits that are faraway!
for this we use diff command again!
(we previously use diff to compare stage and unstage changes)

git diff HEAD~5 HEAD~1      //the order is matter
                            //first commit means make it as old
                            //second commit means make it as new!

git diff 406e4de 19ca155


git diff HEAD~5 HEAD~1 -- "section_3/aliases 4"      //just want to see
                                                     //changes on specific file

git diff HEAD~5 HEAD~1 --name-status


git diff HEAD~5 HEAD~1 --name-only
